Usage: java -jar profilehmm.jar
Parameters:
-a FILE		alignment file in BAM-format OR
-q FILE		read file in FASTQ-format [one of these must be specified; in case of -q an alignment using Bowtie2 is derived]
				-a OR -q must be set
-r FILE		reference genomic sequence file, must be indexed
				must be set in case of -q option
-t FILE		reference transcriptomic sequence file
				optional, but only if -q option is set
-o STRING	output file prefix, should be set in case of -q option
-l INT		maximal read length given [can probably be calculated??] [default: 101]
-p INT		num threads [default: 1]
--gm INT	mapping quality filter for genomic mapping [default: 10]
--tm INT	mapping quality filter for transcriptomic mapping [default: 1]
--profile	calculates error-profile ONLY for genomic mapping, not for transcriptomic mapping!
--ep		only if --profile is active. Shows error-profile as a plot (NOTE: X11-terminal must be activated)
--qual		calculates mean and sd for quality values per mapped base
--refine	uses error-profile derived from selected mapping vs. genome to apply PARMA with the calculated error-profile
--ref-refine	Reference file for PARMA algorithm, if --refine option was activated [default: same as -r file]
--mode		defines mapping algorithm used: bt2, bwa, parma, user [default: BT2]
--parma-mm	ONLY IF "--mode parma": number of average mismatches while applying PARMA algorithm [default: 2]
--parma-ep	ONLY IF "--mode parma": filename of the error profile file
-c			ONLY IF "--mode user": please provide an entire mapping command including all relevant options, e.g. max mismatches etc.
